 How to setup amms from git repository:

 Navigate to the target installation directory (can be arbitrary), for example:

 cd /home/user
 git clone git://github.com/wellcomer/amms.git

 create a symlink:

 ln -s /home/user/amms /usr/lib/amms

 Copy the configuration file conf to /etc/amms/amms.conf
 and edit it to fit your needs.

 Create a database:

 mysql < /usr/lib/amms/doc/db

 Integration with SQUID:

 url_rewrite_program /usr/lib/amms/ammsrd -p squid

 Integration with web server:

 nginx:

 location /ammsd.fcgi {
	fastcgi_pass   127.0.0.1:9000;
	include fastcgi_params;
 }

 location /matchd.fcgi {
 	fastcgi_pass   127.0.0.1:9001;
	include fastcgi_params;
 }

 location /hashd.fcgi {
	fastcgi_pass   127.0.0.1:9002;
	include fastcgi_params;
 }


 Start sequence:

 ammsd
 matchd
 hashd
 amms-tc-squid

 Dependencies:

 ammsc

 perl -MCPAN -e "install HTTP:: Lite"

 ammsd

 FCGI::ProcManager
 Config::General
 Params::Validate
 DBI
 DBD::mysql

 matchd

 Net:: IP:: CMatch

 amms-tc-squid

 File:: Tail


